üì¶ Core Modules (without Auth)
1. Profile & Portfolio (Creatives)

Backend responsibilities:

Endpoints for creating/updating creative profile.

Portfolio CRUD (upload images/videos, add description/tags).

Signed URLs for media upload to storage (S3/GCS).

Basic moderation fields (approved, flagged).

Frontend responsibilities:

Profile form (creative-specific fields: bio, rate card, services).

Portfolio upload UI (images/videos, progress bars).

Gallery view in profile page.

Tags & categories selection.

2. Search & Discovery

Backend responsibilities:

Search/filter by tags, category, services.

Pagination & sorting (rating, price, distance).

Geospatial queries (for ‚Äúnearby creatives‚Äù).

Return summary profiles (not full data).

Frontend responsibilities:

Search bar + filter UI.

Discovery list/grid view of creatives.

Map view (with markers for creatives).

Infinite scroll or ‚Äúload more.‚Äù

3. Map & Geolocation

Backend responsibilities:

Store creatives‚Äô service location (POINT: lat/lng).

Endpoint for ‚Äúnearby creatives within X km.‚Äù

Online/presence indicator via WebSocket/Redis.

Frontend responsibilities:

Ask location permission.

Map screen (markers for photographer/videographer).

Marker legend (different icons/colors).

Click marker ‚Üí open creative profile.

4. Chat & Messaging

Backend responsibilities:

WebSocket server for real-time messaging.

Persist messages in DB (with status: sent/delivered/read).

Message attachments (image/file links).

Presence & typing indicators.

Frontend responsibilities:

Chat UI (WhatsApp-style).

Optimistic sending (pending ‚Üí confirmed).

Local DB (Hive/SQLite) for offline history.

Read receipts, online indicator.

5. Booking & Scheduling

Backend responsibilities:

Booking lifecycle: created ‚Üí paid ‚Üí confirmed ‚Üí completed ‚Üí closed/disputed.

Availability (simple: stored JSON slots; advanced: calendar integration).

Cancel/reschedule logic.

Frontend responsibilities:

Booking form (service type, date, time, notes).

Creative availability picker.

Booking confirmation screen.

Booking history list for both clients & creatives.

6. Payments & Escrow

Backend responsibilities:

Integrate Stripe (or PSP) for marketplace payouts.

Create checkout sessions/payment intents.

Escrow funds until job completion.

Refunds, disputes, payout schedules.

Ledger records for auditing.

Frontend responsibilities:

Payment flow (native card entry or hosted checkout).

Payment status indicators (pending, confirmed, refunded).

Payout settings for creatives (link bank/Stripe account).

Booking ‚Üí payment ‚Üí confirmation UX.

7. Verification & KYC

Backend responsibilities:

Endpoint for ID/license upload.

(MVP) manual verification dashboard for admins.

(v1) integrate KYC vendor (Onfido/Jumio).

Store verification status & badge flag.

Frontend responsibilities:

Verification upload form (ID/license, selfie).

Status indicator (pending/approved/rejected).

Badge display on creative profile.

8. Notifications

Backend responsibilities:

Push notification service (FCM/APNs).

In-app notification feed (DB table + API).

Email notifications for important events.

Frontend responsibilities:

Register push token with backend.

In-app notification list.

Show push for new message, booking update, verification result.

9. Ratings & Reviews

Backend responsibilities:

Endpoints for leaving review after booking.

Store rating + comment.

Aggregate average rating per creative.

Frontend responsibilities:

Post-booking review screen (stars + text).

Reviews list on creative profile.

Show average rating summary.

10. Admin & Moderation

Backend responsibilities:

Admin dashboard for user/creative management.

Approve/reject verification.

Handle reports (spam, abuse, fraud).

Resolve disputes (hold/release payments).

Frontend responsibilities (separate admin panel):

Admin login.

Table views for users/bookings/messages.

Action buttons (suspend, refund, approve).



